Reviewed lifecycle mapping treats CREATING as
provisioning, ACTIVE as success, DELETING as
terminating, and DELETED as the
delete-confirmation target; NEEDS_ATTENTION is
terminal failure without requeue.
Create, update, and delete responses expose
work-request headers, but the SDK exposes no
matching GetWorkRequest or ListWorkRequests
helpers. The runtime records those breadcrumbs
without polling them directly and relies on
lifecycle rereads instead.
Pre-create reuse lists by exact compartmentId
plus displayName, narrows to matching
licenseType summaries, then rereads each
candidate through GetGovernanceInstance so
tenancyNamespace must also match before reuse.
Only displayName, description, licenseType,
freeformTags, and definedTags reconcile in
place; compartmentId, tenancyNamespace,
idcsAccessToken, and systemTags remain
replacement-only drift, and compartment changes
stay out of scope for the published runtime.
end note
